pmos slop-engine
================

This directory (plugins/pmos-toolkit/skills/_shared/slop-engine/) vendors the
deterministic frontend design-slop detection engine from:

    impeccable — https://github.com/pbakaus/impeccable
    Copyright (c) 2026 Paul Bakaus
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0

The rule set (SLOP_RULES in registry.mjs), the pure detection logic
(checks.mjs, color.mjs, constants.mjs, page.mjs, inline-ignores.mjs,
findings.mjs, design-system.mjs), the static-HTML cascade + Node path
(css-cascade.mjs, detect-text.mjs, detect.mjs), the browser detector
(browser.js), and the two-column fixture convention are ported VERBATIM from
impeccable under the terms of the Apache License 2.0 (full text in
LICENSE-impeccable.txt, retained per Apache-2.0 §4(a)).

All pmos-side identifiers, globals, CSS class names, and user-visible strings
have been renamed to pmos-native equivalents per the epic's D-NAMING decision:

    window.impeccableScan        ->  window.pmosDesignScan
    .impeccable-overlay/-label   ->  .pmos-slop-overlay / .pmos-slop-label
    const ANTIPATTERNS           ->  const SLOP_RULES
    __IMPECCABLE_CONFIG__        ->  __PMOS_SLOP_CONFIG__

The generic check-function names (checkBorders, checkColors, …) and rule ids
(side-tab, icon-tile-stack, …) are kept verbatim to preserve upstream parity
and ease future rule re-sync — they are generic descriptors, not branded.

Per the design's Inv-3, the string "impeccable" survives ONLY in this NOTICE,
in LICENSE-impeccable.txt, and in the design-doc lineage prose
(docs/pmos/features/2026-06-24_design-slop-engine/02_design.html#lineage).
A copy of the Apache License 2.0 is at https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Vendored Node parser stack (vendor/parsers.mjs)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The offline Node detection path (detect.mjs) imports a pre-bundled parser stack
so the engine runs with NO `npm install` and NO jsdom at runtime. The bundle is
built with esbuild from the following MIT-licensed libraries (full license texts
in vendor/NOTICE-3RD-PARTY.txt):

    htmlparser2, css-select, css-tree, domutils
    (+ transitive deps: css-what, domhandler, nth-check, boolbase,
       domelementtype, entities)
